   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Connect the serial port on your laptop to the service port
on the HMI module (J405) if the HMI module needs service, and to the
service port on the controller box (J223) if the power module needs
service.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <table frame="none" outputclass="font:10" pgwide="1">
                  <tgroup cols="2">
                     <colspec colname="col1"/>
                     <colspec colname="col2"/>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry colsep="0">
                              <fig>
                                 <title>Service port (J405) on the HMI</title>
                                 <image href="../Images/location_of_service_port_j405_on_the_rear_side_of_the_front_panel_120mm_0000116570.svg"
                                        scalefit="yes"
                                        translate="yes"
                                        xml:lang="en"
                                        placement="inline"/>
                              </fig>
                           </entry>
                           <entry>
                              <fig>
                                 <title>Service port (J223) on the controller box</title>
                                 <image href="../Images/main_controller_service_port_0000116520.svg"
                                        scalefit="yes"
                                        translate="no"
                                        xml:lang="en"
                                        placement="inline"/>
                              </fig>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
               <note>Use the service port cable 940–0024D for the
proper connection of all required signals. If you don’t have
a serial port on your laptop, you can use a USB-to-serial adaptor.
The recommended USB-to-serial adaptors can be found in Service View
or by contacting the technical support.</note>
            </stepxmp>
